<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1343">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/106.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Willard</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-08">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your January 6. Inform King contents Department’s January 5, and also
                                that Department has directed American Consul, Chihuahua, to
                                investigate and report as to killing of two Spanish subjects. You
                                will be informed regarding report.</p>
                            <p>Consul, Hermosillo, reports that Constitutionalist leaders have heard
                                no complaint of mistreatment Spaniards, Parral, but are
                                investigating by telegraph.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>